00:02:03:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:03:190000.Dialogue: Hey, Leonard, where do you come down on giant ants?

00:02:09:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:09:000000.Dialogue: Sheldon says impossible. Howard and I say not only possible, but as a mode of transportation, way cooler than a Batmobile.

00:02:17:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:17:050000.Dialogue: You are ignoring the square-cube law. The giant ant would be crushed under the weight of its own exoskeleton. And for the record, the appropriate ranking of cool modes of transportation is: jet pack, hoverboard, transporter, Batmobile, and then giant ant.

00:02:32:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:32:020000.Dialogue: Seriously? You have nothing better to do than sit around and discuss the possibility of giant ants?

00:02:40:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:40:100000.Dialogue: Perhaps he's at a sensitive point in his monthly cycle.

00:02:53:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:53:000000.Dialogue: But as far back as the 17th century, scientists observed a 33-day fluctuation in men's hormone levels.

00:02:58:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:58:220000.Dialogue: Interesting. That might explain my weepy days in the middle of the month.

00:03:05:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:05:100000.Dialogue: You know what I'm talking about.

00:03:12:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:12:170000.Dialogue: Okay, forget giant ants. How about giant rabbits?

00:03:18:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:18:100000.Dialogue: Big or small, I don't like rabbits. They always look like they're about to say something, but they never do.

00:03:24:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:24:070000.Dialogue: Rabbits do have a respiratory system that would support great size. And on a side note, they are one of the few mammals whose scrotum is in front of the penis.

00:03:35:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:35:170000.Dialogue: Maybe that's what they want to talk about.

00:03:39:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:39:140000.Dialogue: Leonard, where do you stand on giant rabbits and scrotal position?

00:03:46:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:46:000000.Dialogue: Really? Because every time we've talked about unusual animal genitals, you've always had some pretty strong and controversial opinions.

00:03:53:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:53:050000.Dialogue: What do you want from me? I just don't give a rat's ass.

00:03:57:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:57:140000.Dialogue: Would that be a giant rat's ass?

00:04:01:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:01:220000.Dialogue: For the record, giant rats are possible.

00:04:04:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:04:220000.Dialogue: Can we please talk about something else? Maybe something vaguely related to life as we know it on this planet?

00:04:09:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:09:190000.Dialogue: Okay, how about this for a topic: Why is Leonard being a giant douche?

00:04:19:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:19:190000.Dialogue: Of course they are. Leonard's being one.

00:04:23:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:23:100000.Dialogue: Maybe he's having a lover's spat with Penny.

00:04:30:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:30:100000.Dialogue: I don't want to talk about it.

00:04:31:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:31:190000.Dialogue: But I sense you're going to and I don't want to hear about it. Excuse me.

00:04:36:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:36:120000.Dialogue: What'd you do, Romeo? You pour maple syrup all over your body and ask her if she was in the mood for a short stack?

00:04:46:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:46:140000.Dialogue: Did you think it would be funny to put on a pair of her panties and jump around, but it wound up just creeping her out?

00:04:55:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:55:190000.Dialogue: I'm just asking, dude. It happens.

00:05:01:190000.Speaker: Stuart
00:05:01:190000.Dialogue: You guys still on for bowling tonight?

00:05:04:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:04:050000.Dialogue: Oh, yes. In fact, I've prepared some trash talk for the occasion. You bowl like your mama.

00:05:12:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:12:000000.Dialogue: Unless, of course, she bowls well. In which case, you bowl nothing like her.

00:05:18:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:18:190000.Dialogue: That is what is referred to as a burn on you.

00:05:24:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:24:140000.Dialogue: Did you ask her to start waxing?

00:05:30:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:30:220000.Dialogue: While making love, did you accidentally spank your own ass and cry out, "Mommy"?

00:05:43:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:43:170000.Dialogue: I'm walking away from you now.

00:05:48:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:48:020000.Dialogue: Yeah, I think we're getting close.

00:05:52:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:52:020000.Dialogue: Did you take a Benadryl and fall asleep while pleasuring her? Because you can die that way.

00:05:58:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:58:140000.Dialogue: Oh, that would be a good way to go.

00:06:10:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:10:220000.Dialogue: You don't have to come if you don't want to.

00:06:13:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:13:020000.Dialogue: No, no, it's okay. I mean, let's face it, you guys would get creamed without me.

00:06:17:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:17:070000.Dialogue: We would indeed. In this particular case, your lack of femininity works to our advantage.

00:06:25:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:25:020000.Dialogue: It's always nice chatting with you, Sheldon.

00:06:38:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:38:020000.Dialogue: Please reserve that butch spirit for the lanes.

00:06:49:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:49:020000.Dialogue: I thought you were bringing your own bowling shoes.

00:06:51:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:51:140000.Dialogue: These are my own bowling shoes.

00:06:57:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:57:000000.Dialogue: I know where my feet have been.

00:07:08:100000.Speaker: Stuart
00:07:08:100000.Dialogue: Albino Bob couldn't make it, so I brought a substitute. I believe some of you know Wil Wheaton.

00:07:20:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:20:050000.Dialogue: Well, well, well. If it isn't Wil Wheaton, the Green Goblin to my Spider-Man. the Pope Paul V to my Galileo, the Internet Explorer to my Firefox.

00:07:32:140000.Speaker: Wil
00:07:32:140000.Dialogue: You're not still carrying a grudge because I beat you at that card tournament, are you?

00:07:37:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:37:100000.Dialogue: I'm the proud owner of WilWheatonstinks.com,.net, and.org.

00:07:42:100000.Speaker: Wil
00:07:42:100000.Dialogue: It tells me that I am living rent-free right here.

00:07:48:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:48:140000.Dialogue: Oh, I'm ready. I don't know if Stuart told you what you're up against tonight, but before you stands the co-captain of the East Texas Christian Youth Holy Roller Bowling League championship team. Seven- to 12-year-old division. Also, Penny's pretty good.

00:08:12:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:12:100000.Dialogue: Oh, foolish Wil Wheaton, it was never off.

00:08:19:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:19:190000.Dialogue: Yes! A common spare. The Miss Congeniality of the bowling pageant. Before you jump on Twitter to tout your modest accomplishment, watch how it's really done. I am the ball. My thoughts are its thoughts. Its holes are my holes.

00:08:53:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:53:170000.Dialogue: Hey, I just wanted to tell you I'm a big fan.

00:08:59:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:59:220000.Dialogue: I'm sure you're probably sick of Star Trek questions, but Whoopi Goldberg-- you ever hit that?

00:09:08:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:08:050000.Dialogue: Ah, beer. The magic elixir that can turn this poor, shy Indian boy into the life of the party.

00:09:26:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:26:170000.Dialogue: Yes. I love chili cheese fries.

00:09:32:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:32:000000.Dialogue: No reason. I'm just glad to hear you're comfortable saying you love something.

00:09:37:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:37:190000.Dialogue: Do you really want to get into this right now?

00:09:40:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:40:050000.Dialogue: Get into what? Why wouldn't you love the chili cheese fries? They've been in your life a long time. They make you happy. They deserve to know.

00:09:49:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:49:050000.Dialogue: Look, you just caught me by surprise last night. I didn't know what to say.

00:09:53:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:53:170000.Dialogue: Okay, well, now you've had some time to think about it. So, what do you want to say?

00:09:58:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:58:070000.Dialogue: How can you not be sure?

00:10:00:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:00:020000.Dialogue: Okay, this isn't the place to have this conversation.

00:10:02:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:02:020000.Dialogue: No, the place to have the conversation was in bed after I said, "I love yo"" and you said, "Thank you. Good night""

00:10:48:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:48:070000.Dialogue: I've been familiarizing myself with female emotional crises by studying the comic strip Cathy.

00:10:57:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:57:020000.Dialogue: When she's upset, she says, "Ack!" and eats ice cream.

00:11:09:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:09:020000.Dialogue: If you were a cat, I would have brought you a lasagna.

00:11:14:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:14:070000.Dialogue: Did Leonard send you over here?

00:11:16:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:16:070000.Dialogue: No, we haven't spoken since your abrupt departure last night caused us to forfeit to Stuart and his dastardly ringer Wil Wheaton.

00:11:25:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:25:190000.Dialogue: I'm not too proud to admit that I cried myself to sleep.

00:11:30:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:30:120000.Dialogue: And let me tell you, sleep did not come easily with Leonard in the next room singing along with Alanis Morrisette.

00:11:40:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:40:190000.Dialogue: No. Clearly another woman in dire need of ice cream.

00:11:44:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:44:140000.Dialogue: All right, Sheldon, what part of this is supposed to make me feel better?

00:11:47:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:47:190000.Dialogue: The part where I tell you I've engineered a rematch with Stuart's team for tonight.

00:11:53:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:53:020000.Dialogue: Oh, honey, I don't know. Things are a little weird with Leonard right now.

00:11:57:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:57:000000.Dialogue: You want me to remove him from the team? I'm the captain. I can do that.

00:12:00:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:00:220000.Dialogue: No, no, that's okay. Just let me talk to him, and I'll get back to you.

00:12:06:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:06:020000.Dialogue: When are you going to talk to him?

00:12:11:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:11:020000.Dialogue: He's in the laundry room now. Now woulbe a good time.

00:12:13:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:13:100000.Dialogue: You're not gonna leave me alone until I do it, are you?

00:12:16:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:16:170000.Dialogue: Oh, I think we both know the answer to that question.

00:12:25:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:25:220000.Dialogue: I think we should talk now.

00:12:27:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:27:170000.Dialogue: Wha...? No, it's okay. We don't have to talk 'cause there's nothing to talk about. Everything's good.

00:12:35:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:35:140000.Dialogue: So, you didn't get all snarky 'cause I said somethingice to a bowl of chili fries?

00:12:40:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:40:120000.Dialogue: All right, maybe I overreacted. So we're in two different places emotionally. So what? And maybe I'm a little ahead of you. That's fine. In fact, it makes sense, 'cause let's face it, I've been in this relationship two years longer than you.

00:12:57:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:57:170000.Dialogue: Look, Leonard, you have how much I care about you. It's just that I've said the "L" word too soon before, and it didn't work out very well.

00:13:06:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:06:050000.Dialogue: Really? I wouldn't know what that's like.

00:13:09:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:09:100000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. You know what I'm talking about, though.

00:13:16:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:16:020000.Dialogue: Yes, that's what I'm telling you. We are good. We are great.

00:13:20:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:20:220000.Dialogue: All right! Fence mended, problem swept under the rug.

00:13:23:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:23:000000.Dialogue: Time to bowl! Yes, I was eavesdropping. There's a lot at stake here.

00:13:32:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:32:020000.Dialogue: Attention, all bowlers: I've taken the liberty of having these made for our rematch.

00:13:41:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:41:070000.Dialogue: No, not The Wesley Crushers. The Wesley Crushers.

00:13:46:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:46:020000.Dialogue: Wesley Crusher was Wil Wheaton's character on Star Trek.

00:13:51:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:51:100000.Dialogue: It's a blindingly clever play on words. By appropriating his character's name and adding the S, we imply that we we'll be the crushers of Wesley.

00:14:02:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:02:000000.Dialogue: Okay, I'm sorry, honey, but The Wesley Crushers sounds like a bunch of people who like Wesley Crusher.

00:14:06:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:06:170000.Dialogue: No! Again, it's not the Wesley Crushers. It's the Wesley Crushers.

00:14:12:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:12:120000.Dialogue: No, if you want it to mean you're crushing Wesley, it'd be the Wesley Crushers.

00:14:18:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:18:070000.Dialogue: Do you people even hear yourselves? It's not The Wesley Crushers. It's not The Wesley Crushers. It's The Wesley Crushers.

00:14:25:190000.Speaker: Wil
00:14:25:190000.Dialogue: Hey, look. They named their team after me.

00:14:29:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:29:190000.Dialogue: No, it's not the... Never mind.

00:14:35:050000.Speaker: Stuart
00:14:35:050000.Dialogue: So, we're all clear on the bet and the stakes?

00:14:39:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:39:020000.Dialogue: Oh, yes. The losers will be publicly humiliated in a fashion to be chosen by the victor. I plan on having you publish a scientific paper expounding the discredited Velikovsky hypothesis.

00:14:56:050000.Speaker: Wil
00:14:56:050000.Dialogue: Hey, Sheldon, I just wanted you to know that I'm really looking forward to wiping the floor with you.

00:15:02:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:02:100000.Dialogue: Oh, yes? Well, before I respond, let me ask you a question. Is your mother a good or poor bowler?

00:15:17:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:17:220000.Dialogue: No, after you... as we are currently crushing you, Wesley.

00:15:25:020000.Speaker: Wil
00:15:25:020000.Dialogue: It's customary for the player on the right-hand lane to bowl first.

00:15:41:140000.Speaker: Wil
00:15:41:140000.Dialogue: It's a custom, not a rule.

00:15:46:170000.Speaker: Wil
00:15:46:170000.Dialogue: That's right, Sheldon. Embrace the dark side.

00:15:53:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:53:070000.Dialogue: That's not even from your franchise!

00:15:57:000000.Speaker: Stuart
00:15:57:000000.Dialogue: I, um, I want you to know that even though we're on opposite sides, I, I bear you no ill will.

00:16:04:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:04:170000.Dialogue: Thank you, Stuart. It's nice to know.

00:16:07:020000.Speaker: Stuart
00:16:07:020000.Dialogue: Mm-hmm, mm-hmm. People from opposite sides often have good relationships. You know, Romeo and Juliet... Tony and Maria from West Side Story, what's-his-name and the big blue chick in Avatar.

00:16:48:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:48:070000.Dialogue: It's good that we got out and did something physical.

00:16:50:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:50:070000.Dialogue: Mm-hmm. Gets us out of our heads.

00:17:02:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:02:070000.Dialogue: Mm-hmm, and someday-- we don't know when-- maybe you'll love me back.

00:17:15:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:15:020000.Dialogue: Excuse me. I don't know who you're chanting for as I am currently the ball.

00:17:22:100000.Speaker: All
00:17:22:100000.Dialogue: The ball! The ball! The ball! The ball! The ball! The ball!

00:17:42:050000.Speaker: Wil
00:17:42:050000.Dialogue: I'm glad you patched things up with your boyfriend.

00:17:47:000000.Speaker: Wil
00:17:47:000000.Dialogue: It's always tough when the "L" bomb gets dropped and you're not ready for it.

00:17:52:050000.Speaker: Wil
00:17:52:050000.Dialogue: I dated this one girl, and I told her that I loved her, and she said she wasn't sure. And she strung me along for almost two years. It was brutal.

00:18:05:100000.Speaker: Wil
00:18:05:100000.Dialogue: Thanks. I wish she had just broken up with me right there, and put me out of my misery.

00:18:21:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:21:170000.Dialogue: Did you let Wil Wheaton get in your head?

00:18:25:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:25:190000.Dialogue: He's evil. He plays evil mind games. Did he tell you his grandmother died?

00:18:31:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:31:120000.Dialogue: Well, if he does, don't believe it. He's not above playing the dead meemaw card.

00:18:41:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:41:100000.Dialogue: Enjoy the accolades now, Wil Wheaton, but like your time on Star Trek: Next Generation, your smug self-satisfaction will be short-lived.

00:18:52:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:52:050000.Dialogue: All right, remember, his meemaw's alive and be the ball.

00:18:57:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:57:070000.Dialogue: We really need a strike here.

00:18:59:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:59:190000.Dialogue: So just take your time and concentrate.

00:19:03:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:03:170000.Dialogue: Yeah, you are! Just back off!

00:19:05:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:05:140000.Dialogue: Okay, I'm sorry. I'll shut up.

00:19:12:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:12:020000.Dialogue: Fine. Just tell me what to do, and I'll do it.

00:19:16:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:16:000000.Dialogue: No... this isn't fair to you, Leonard. I'm sorry.

00:19:23:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:23:020000.Dialogue: Wait! Where are you going? Penny, come back! I'll get you ice cream!

00:19:29:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:29:100000.Dialogue: Are you insane? If she leaves, it's over!

00:19:32:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:32:170000.Dialogue: I'm pretty sure it's already over.

00:19:42:170000.Speaker: Wil
00:19:42:170000.Dialogue: Do you think I would really break up a couple just to win a bowling match?

00:20:02:050000.Speaker: Stuart
00:20:02:050000.Dialogue: Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, yeah, I'm telling you, the Match.com chicks are much looser than on eHarmony.

00:20:10:050000.Speaker: Stuart
00:20:10:050000.Dialogue: You know, I-I gotta call you back. I won a bet, and it's time to collect.

00:20:28:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:20:28:120000.Dialogue: I don't know about you, but I feel empowered.
